# GitHub Pages deployment

The public site is **static** (no FastAPI on Pages). It is built from **`docs/`**, deployed by **GitHub Actions** (`.github/workflows/pages.yml`) on push to **`main`**, with optional **manual runs** (**Actions → Deploy GitHub Pages → Run workflow**).

## When to refresh `docs/`

After **SQLite topic data** changes (e.g. **`import-bullets`**, or anything that would change **`/`** or **`/episodes`** in the local app), or after edits that affect **exported HTML/JSON** (templates with `static_site`, `bilradio/export_pages.py`, `bilradio/web/static/*`), run from repo root:

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m bilradio.cli export-github-pages
```

Default output is **`docs/`** (`--output` / `-o` to override). **`--cname`** defaults to **`bilradio.jacobworsoe.dk`** (written to **`docs/CNAME`**).

Then **commit and push** the updated **`docs/`** (including **`docs/api/*.json`**, HTML, **`docs/CNAME`**, **`docs/.nojekyll`**) so the workflow publishes the new snapshot. **`data/`** stays gitignored; only the **export** lands in git.

## Live app vs snapshot

- **Local:** **`bilradio serve`** — dynamic API, RSS sync, ingest, clear error on **`/episodes`**.
- **Pages:** same templates with **`static_site`**: loads **`/api/*.json`** files; episodes actions are read-only (alerts). Custom domain: **https://bilradio.jacobworsoe.dk/** (also **https://jacobworsoe.github.io/bilradio-transcriper/**).

## Repo settings

Repository must allow **GitHub Pages** (public repo or Enterprise). **Settings → Pages → Source: GitHub Actions**. Enter the **custom domain** in Settings if DNS is set; **`docs/CNAME`** should match.

## Do not

- Expect the **FastAPI server** to run on Pages.
- Use **`upload-pages-artifact@v4.0.0`** without fixing **dotfiles**: it drops **`.nojekyll`**; this workflow uses **`v3`** for that reason unless a newer v4 adds hidden-file support.
